<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Entirely white with a slight ochreous tinge, veins slightly darker than foreground. Below a black streak along the costa of forewings and the veins more contrasting in the distal part of wings. Females larger than males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
